content.text: How to Remove Duplicates From a Python List
Learn how to remove duplicates from a List in Python.
content.html: Learn how to remove duplicates from a List in Python.

content.code_html:
mylist = ["a", "b", "a", "c", "c"]
mylist = list(dict.fromkeys(mylist))
print(mylist)

content.text: First we have a List that contains duplicates:
content.html: First we have a List that contains duplicates:

content.code_html:
mylist = ["a", "b", "a", "c", "c"]
 mylist = list(dict.fromkeys(mylist))
print(mylist)

content.text: Create a dictionary, using the List items as keys. This will automatically remove any duplicates because dictionaries cannot have duplicate keys.
content.html: Create a dictionary, using the List items as keys. This will automatically remove any duplicates because dictionaries cannot have duplicate keys.

content.code_html:
mylist = ["a", "b", "a", "c", "c"]
 mylist = list( dict.fromkeys(mylist) )
print(mylist)

content.text: Then, convert the dictionary back into a list:
content.html: Then, convert the dictionary back into a list:

content.code_html:
mylist = ["a", "b", "a", "c", "c"]
 mylist = list( dict.fromkeys(mylist) )
print(mylist)

content.text: Now we have a List without any duplicates, and it has the same order as the original List.
content.html: Now we have a List without any duplicates, and it has the same order as the original List.

mylist = list(dict.fromkeys(mylist))

content.text: If you like to have a function where you can send your lists, and get them back without duplicates, you can create a function and insert the code from the example above.
content.html: If you like to have a function where you can send your lists, and get them back without duplicates, you can create a function and insert the code from the example above.

content.code_html:
def my_function(x):
  return list(dict.fromkeys(x))

mylist = my_function(["a", "b", "a", "c", "c"])

print(mylist)
